<taxonomicName authority="Šifner, 2008" authorityName="Šifner" authorityYear="2008" box="[663,776,1021,1045]" class="Insecta" family="Scathophagidae" genus="Microprosopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ozerovi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[663,685,1022,1045]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[698,776,1022,1045]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">ozerovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[783,865,1021,1044]" pageId="4" pageNumber="107" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
– bristles between lobes of abdominal sternite 5 present, incision of abdominal sternite 4 distinct, praegonite beakshaped (
<figureCitation box="[240,337,1085,1109]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="5.[113,152,1497,1516]" captionTargetBox="[153,1051,209,1447]" captionTargetId="figure-14@5.[149,1053,209,1453]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs. 7-11. 7: Amaurosoma bernasconii sp. nov., female, allotype, abdominal sternites 4 to 7. 8-9: Microprosopa ozerovi sp. nov., male, paratype; 10-11: Norellisoma vonickai sp. nov., female. 8 – abdominal sternites 3 to 5; 9 – praegonite; 10 – abdominal sternites 5 to 7; 11 – abdominal sternite 8. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs. 8, 10); 0.1 mm (Figs. 7, 9, 11)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468113" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468113/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">Figs. 8-9</figureCitation>
); 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sifner" authorityYear="1981" box="[358,517,1085,1109]" class="Insecta" family="Scathophagidae" genus="Microprosopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoberlandti">
<emphasis box="[358,380,1086,1109]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[393,517,1086,1109]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">hoberlandti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
– bristles between lobes of abdominal sternite 5 missing, abdominal sternite 4 oval, praegonite with two apical bristles (
<bibRefCitation author="SIFNER F." box="[817,950,1116,1141]" pageId="4" pageNumber="107" pagination="95 - 104" refId="ref3037" refString="SIFNER F. 1981: Les resultats de l'expedition entomologique Tchecoslovaque-iranienne a l'Iran en 1973. Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae 40: 95 - 104." type="journal article" year="1981">ŠIFNER 1981</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
